  <roomsDescription><![CDATA[<p><strong>Standard Hotels</strong></p>
<p>Balestrand, <a data-udi="umb://document/e6e72ed8f54b4b799df9821bf732b69d" href="https://www.inghams.co.uk/destinations/norway/balestrand/midtnes-hotel">Hotel Midtnes</a> ★★+ A small, homely hotel with a relaxed atmosphere, attentive personal service from your host, Jon, and panoramic views.  The Midtnes is located in a peaceful spot just next door to St. Olaf's Church and enjoys its own fjord side garden as well as offers panoramic fjord views from its sun terrace. Guests here are sure of a warm welcome.</p>
<p>Loen, <a data-udi="umb://document/7780b99803294b0f8a9519ed836b9830" href="https://www.inghams.co.uk/destinations/norway/loen/loenfjord-hotel">Hotel Loenfjord</a> ★★★+ A lovely friendly and informal riverside hotel recently built in traditional style on the shores of the fjord with bright comfortable bedrooms and attractively furnished public areas. Guests here enjoy the hotel's peaceful riverside setting and a good value base from which to explore this beautiful region. Guests have full use of the facilities at the <a href="https://www.inghams.co.uk/destinations/norway/loen/loenfjord-hotel">Hotel Alexandra</a> a minute's walk away.</p>
<p>Alesund, <a data-udi="umb://document/89e354afa6824ae197da03b9604055e7" href="https://www.inghams.co.uk/destinations/norway/alesund/first-hotel-atlantica">First Hotel Atlantica</a> ★★★+ A smart hotel that is ideally located in the heart of Ålesund directly opposite the picturesque old fishing port and Brosundet canal. The harbour is only a short walk away, making the hotel a great base from which to explore. Our prices are based on bed and breakfast only, but with a daily packed lunch included. There is also a good selection of restaurants serving international cuisine nearby.</p>
<p><strong>OR</strong></p>
<p><strong>Superior Hotels</strong></p>
<p>Balestrand, <a data-udi="umb://document/d26dcba440054402b9ccfe7166c1ad56" href="https://www.inghams.co.uk/destinations/norway/balestrand/kviknes-hotel">Hotel Kviknes</a> ★★★★ This wonderfully atmospheric historic dates back to 1752. Today with its modern amenities, main wing and attentive personal service it remains one of Fjord Norway’s best loved, family-run properties. The attractive original Swiss style wing radiates personality and soul, with an absolutely magnificent scenic fjord-side location and panoramic views across the Sognefjord.</p>
<p>Loen, <a data-udi="umb://document/fbdb2d63e0f24d7fb8fbb7a20fdd9578" href="https://www.inghams.co.uk/destinations/norway/loen/alexandra-hotel">Hotel Alexandra</a> ★★★★+ Built in 1884 the Alexandra is an intimate and truly special fifth generation family-run hotel steeped in tradition and set in the heart of this breathtakingly beautiful region. As one of Norway’s very best hotels, and is a favourite in our programme, it combines genuine hospitality, exceptional cuisine, gardens and extensive pool and spa facilities.</p>
<p>Ålesund, <a data-udi="umb://document/7ce188510b05444696b765f7f5cc643b" href="https://www.inghams.co.uk/destinations/norway/alesund/hotel-brosundet">Hotel Brosundet</a> ★★★★ One of Norway’s ‘Historic Hotels’, the Hotel Brosundet enjoys an excellent location right on the quayside on the Brosundet canal and overlooking the old fishing port. The attractively-furnished hotel is located inside an old warehouse still featuring exposed beams and the lobby area and restaurant have recently been renovated. Ålesund centre for a selection of restaurants and shops is right on your doorstep, whilst the harbour is a pleasant 8 minute walk away.</p>
<p> </p>]]></roomsDescription>
